@Database CFG_CtrlScrPrefs

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "HBBS:System/Data/CtrlScrPrefs - Config File"

  Description
  ===========

  The HBBS:System/Data/CtrlScrPrefs file defines the screen settings
  for the control screen.

  The file is generated and maintained by the Control itself, but
  there is currently one option that you may want to set yourself.

  Options:
  ========

    UseBackfill=<Boolean>           @{" More... " link CFG_UseBackFill}

@EndNode

@Node CFG_UseBackfill "UseBackfill"

  UseBackfill=<Boolean>

    E.G.

    UseBackfill=NO

    Defaults to YES

    When Control is opened on its own screen with a depth of 4 or more
    (16+ colours) HydraBBS will change the colours of the screen so that
    the first 8 colours are the usual ANSI colours, then the next four
    colours will be the normal intuition colours.

    When this is done the backgrounds of windows and gadgets will still
    appear using colour index 0 (which is black, instead of grey) so we
    have to use a backfill function, which is called by intuition whenever
    a window or background needs to be re/drawn.

    This function was giving me greif during the development of HydraBBS
    but now seems to work fine, but if you have problems opening certain
    screen modes or corrupted window graphics then try disabling the
    backfill function by using this option.

    Without this option enabled HydraBBS will look *very* strange indeed.

    Backfill is NEVER used on screens with a depth of 3 or less
    (less than 16 colours)

@EndNode


